    <h2>A/B testing your Kenyan landing page turns guesswork into data, and improves conversions from every Ksh of ad spend over time.</h2>
    <p>A/B testing shows two versions of a landing page to different visitors simultaneously and measures which version produces more conversions. For Kenyan businesses running Google Ads at Ksh 20,000 per month or more, A/B testing is the most direct way to improve return on ad spend without increasing budget.</p>

    <p>The highest-impact elements to test on Kenyan landing pages: headline text (benefit-focused vs urgency-focused), CTA button text ("WhatsApp Us Now" vs "Get a Free Quote" vs "Call Us Today"), hero image type (business outcome photo vs product photo vs founder photo), form length (3 fields vs 5 fields), and social proof type (text testimonials vs Google review screenshots vs video testimonials). Start with one element per test, changing multiple elements simultaneously makes it impossible to know which change produced the result.</p>

    <p>Testing tool options: GA4 built-in A/B testing (replacing the discontinued Google Optimize) is free for Kenyan businesses with Google Analytics 4 installed. VWO (Visual Website Optimizer) provides more advanced testing capabilities from $99 per month, appropriate for businesses running significant Kenyan ad budgets.</p>

    <p>Minimum test duration for Kenyan landing pages: 2 to 4 weeks. Kenyan traffic volumes on most business landing pages require this duration to reach statistical significance. A test run for 3 days with 50 visitors cannot produce reliable conclusions, the data variance is too high.</p>

